<a id="sortnameguide-<% $_[0] %>" href="#sortnameguide-<% $_[0] %>"><b>&bull;</b></a>
</%def>

<p><b>Style Notes for Sort Names</b></p>

<p>
	<& .StyleGuideLink, "general" &>
	The "sort name" is the name that will be used when the artist is listed in a 
	list with other artists, so that all the artists that start with <i>The</i>
	will not end up under T.&nbsp; This also applies to artists who have a regular
	names like <i>Eric Clapton</i> but not bands that have ficticious names like
	<i>Cypress Hill</i>.&nbsp; Sort names should contain all the accented
	characters that are present in the name of the artist.
</p>

<p>
	<& .StyleGuideLink, "definite-article" &>
Non-english articles like <i>La</i>, <i>El</i>, <i>Los</i>, <i>Le</i>
should be treated like the english aritcle <i>The</i>.
</p>

<p>
	<& .StyleGuideLink, "DJ" &>
	Artists with
	the letters <i>DJ</i> (for Disc Jockey) should not include any
	periods for the <i>DJ</i> portion in the name or sort name.
</p>

<p>
	<& .StyleGuideLink, "personal-titles" &>
	Prefix titles like <i>Dr.</i> should be treated as if they were first names. 
</p>

<p><b>Sort Name Examples:</b></p>

<blockquote class="StyleExample">
<table width="100%">
      <tr>
         <td width="50%"><b>Name</b></td>
         <td width="50%"><b>Sort Name</b></td>
      </tr>
